# v0.56 ‚Äî Screen Shake on Heavy Hits + Camera2D

### New Files
- `scripts/camera_shake.gd` ‚Äî Reusable Camera2D shake component
  - Triggered on heavy hits (player or captain attacks)
  - Trauma decay over time with optional frequency
  - Configurable intensity and duration per source
  - Singleton-like access via `get_tree().root.get_camera_2d()

### Updated
- `scenes/game.tscn` / chapter scenes ‚Äî added Camera2D node with camera_shake.gd
- `scripts/player.gd` ‚Äî calls `camera.shake()` on heavy attack land
- `scripts/skeleton_captain.gd` ‚Äî calls `camera.shake()` on shield bash / charge impact
- `scripts/skeleton_archer.gd` ‚Äî light shake on arrow hit

### Visual Polish
- Impact feedback: screen shake on heavy hits makes combat feel weightier
- Camera stays at 640√ó360, shake applied as offset (no resolution change)
- Different trauma levels: player heavy = 0.6s @ 0.4, captain charge = 0.8s @ 0.5, arrow = 0.3s @ 0.2

