# v0.57 ‚Äî Hit-Stop (Freeze Frames on Impact)

### New Files
- `scripts/hit_stop.gd` ‚Äî Global HitStop autoload
  - `trigger(ms)` pauses `Engine.time_scale = 0` for N milliseconds
  - Accumulates freeze time if triggered again while frozen (combo feel)
  - `trigger_light()` = 80ms default, `trigger_heavy()` = 150ms
  - Capped at `max_freeze_ms` (250ms) to prevent stunlock
  - Uses `get_tree().create_timer(..., true)` with physics process

### Updated
- `project.godot` ‚Äî added HitStop to `[autoload]` alongside ScreenShake
- `scripts/player.gd` ‚Äî HitStop on take_damage (light/heavy) + on attack hit
- `scripts/skeleton.gd` ‚Äî HitStop on attack_hitbox body_entered
- `scripts/skeleton_captain.gd` ‚Äî HitStop.heavy() on attack_hitbox connect
- `scripts/arrow.gd` ‚Äî HitStop on player hit

### Design Rationale
- Freeze frames make impacts feel weightier without changing any damage numbers
- Light freeze on normal hits (80ms), heavy on big hits (150ms)
- Combo accumulation prevents rapid-fire attacks from feeling weaker
- 250ms cap keeps game responsive ‚Äî never freezes longer than 1/4 second

